<h2>The Big Players</h2>

<p>The US dollar is by far the most traded currency, making up close to 85 percent of all trades. Second is the euro, which is part of 39 percent of all currency trades, and third is the Japanese yen at 19 percent. (Note: these figures do not total 100 percent because there are two sides to every FX transaction).

According to the 2015 Euromoney survey, Citigroup and Deutsche Bank were the two biggest banks in the forex market, combining for more that 30 percent of the global market share.

